lli, and James Ensor, artists who shared a concern with painting and temporality that is all but forgotten today, having been eclipsed by the ideals of Impressionism. Young's highly original study situates later Realism for the first time within the larger social, political, and economic framework and argues for its centrality in understanding the development of modern art.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Feb 2020) 0aArtxPolitical aspects. 0aImpressionism (Art) 0aImpressionism (Art). 0aPainting, Frenchx19th century. 0aPainting, Frenchy19th century. 0aRealism in art. 0aTime in art. 7aART / History / Modern (late 19th Century to 1945).2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook Package 2014-2015z978311067250340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300212853423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300212853.jpg  a978-3-11-067250-3  YUP eBook Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aEBA_FAO